\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. M. minimus} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 284 (1753). Glabrous. Leaves linear, entire, in a basal rosette. Flowers pale greenish-yellow. Perianth-segments 3-4 mm, linear-oblong, spurred at the base. Honey-leaves with a short, oblong limb. Pedicels 5-12 cm, slender in fruit, longer than the fruiting receptacle. Achenes 1-1·5 mm, keeled, very shortly beaked. 2n = 16, 28. {\i Open habitats, especially when seasonally flooded. Most of Europe, but rare in the extreme north and south and in the islands.} Au Be Bl Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs(N, B, C, W, K, E) Si Su Tu.
