\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs with erect, woody stock. Leaves 1- to 3-ternate. Flowers hermaphrodite. Perianth-segments 5, petaloid. Honey-leaves 5, more or less tubular, each with a flat limb and a backwardly directed nectar-secreting spur. Stamens numerous, the innermost represented by scarious staminodes. Carpels free. Follicles several, free.
\par

\par

